past: two boys live with their parents in a hous\lang1033\f1 e in a bay outside of the town\lang1029\f0 . \lang1033\f1 T\lang1029\f0 he family is quite average, nobody stands out, they don't have much money, parents don't have many ambitions (fisherman) and they let the old house slowly to fall apart. John realises soon that he hates the place and that it holds him back, and he leaves when he is 18 for a police academy in Fort William. His brother never truly forgives him. John was always a kind a loner, his job suits him, he doesn't talk to his colleagues much and is perfectly ok with drinking a beer from a can in front of a TV in the evening and going to sleep. After he left, Al sought company among the local boys and girls in Mallaig. He falls in love with a girl when he is 18 and he marries her 5 years later. The sea is always present in the lives of everyone.Their father dies before the wedding, the mother soon after that, not entountering the first grandchild, and the family decides to stay in the house by the sea. John doesn't hit it off very well with Janet and after the wedding, he doesn't come back much, only for a few days each summer. The already broken family ties gets broken even more and John, though struggling to find a way to his brother, never truly succeeds, with his brother unable to forgive him for leaving. He has his own life now and doesn't have to impress his brother, who in his eyes lives a boring life in the city. \par
Al is sort of happy in the place where he grew, never really haunted by any ghosts of the past in that place. \par
The tragedy happens when Mai is four. Week before that, John sees his brother for the last time alive. He senses tension between the couple but as always this visit of his is sort of awkward and when he tries to talk to Al, he pushes him away, \par
What happened that day? The family had a picking on a rock overeseeing the sea. Al was standing on the cliff when a bird startled him, he fell over and hit the water thirty feet below. The autopsy stated he was alive for a while longer but unconcious and quickly drowned, roughed by the rocks that the waves carried him against. The investigation soon ended, stating an accident and no outside influence. \par
Mai is assigned to John's care. She's a weirdly quiet child \lang1033\f1 [...]\lang1029\f0\par
He changes a little on the outside, but the tragedy hardens him. Now his traits may take over his behaviour. \par
